claim.claim-text:
1. A personal computer configured for use by at least one individual user and for connection to a network of computers including the Internet, said computer comprising:
a microchip comprising at least two general purpose microprocessors and at least one internal hardware firewall;
one said internal hardware firewall is configured to protect a hardware protected side of the microchip's hardware and to separate the hardware protected side of the microchip's hardware from an network side that is not protected by said internal hardware firewall;

at least one said general purpose microprocessor is located within said hardware protected side of the microchip;
at least one said general purpose microprocessor is located within said network side of the microchip, and said network side of the microchip being configured for connection to said network of computers and being located between said internal hardware firewall and a wired or wireless network connection to said network of computers,

said at least one general purpose microprocessor located within said network side of the microchip being a separate component from said internal hardware firewall;
said internal hardware firewall is configured to make said hardware protected side of the microchip inaccessible by a network including the Internet when the computer is connected to said network;
said internal hardware firewall by its location does not restrict access by the network to the network side of the microchip, thereby not restricting network operations conducted by the computer with said network, which network operations are conducted in said network side using said at least one network side general purpose microprocessor of the microchip when the computer is connected to said network;
said computer including at least one said-general purpose microprocessor that is not a hardware network communication component and is located in said network side; and
said microchip is surrounded by a first Faraday Cage.

13. A microchip configured for use in a personal computer by at least one individual user and for connection to a network of computers including the Internet, said microchip comprising:
a general purpose microprocessor, the general purpose microprocessor including at least two processing units; and
an internal hardware firewall;
said internal hardware firewall is configured to protect a hardware protected side of the microchip's hardware and to separate a hardware protected side of the microchip's hardware from an unprotected network side of the microchip's hardware, said unprotected network side being configured for connection to a network;
at least one of the processing units of the general purpose microprocessor is located within said hardware protected side;
one or more of the processing units of the general purpose microprocessor is located within said unprotected network side that is located between said internal hardware firewall and a wired or wireless network connection,

at least one said network side processing unit is not a network communications component, and said network side processing units being separate from said internal hardware firewall;
said internal hardware firewall is configured to make said hardware protected side of the microchip inaccessible by a network including the Internet when the computer is connected to said network;
said internal hardware firewall by its location does not restrict access by the network to the unprotected network side of the microchip, thereby not restricting network operations conducted by the microchip with said network, which network operations are conducted in said unprotected network side using said at least one network side processing unit of at least one said general purpose microprocessor of the microchip when the computer is connected to said network; and
said microchip is surrounded by a first Faraday Cage.

23. A personal computer configured for use by at least one individual user and for connection to a network of computers including the Internet, said computer comprising:
two or more general purpose microprocessors; and
an internal hardware firewall;
said internal hardware firewall is configured to protect a hardware protected side of the computer's hardware and to separate the hardware protected side of the computer's hardware from an unprotected network side of the computer's hardware that is not protected by said internal hardware firewall, said unprotected network side being configured to connect to a network;
at least one said general purpose microprocessor is located within said hardware protected side of the computer that is protected by at least said internal hardware firewall;
at least one of said general purpose microprocessors located within said unprotected network side that is located between said internal hardware firewall and a wired or wireless network connection,

at least one said network side general purpose microprocessor located within said unprotected network side of the computer is not a network communications component, and said at least one network side general purpose microprocessor located within the unprotected network side being separate from said internal hardware firewall;
said internal hardware firewall is configured to make said hardware protected side of the microchip inaccessible by a network including the Internet when the computer is connected to said network;
said internal hardware firewall by its location does not restrict access by the network to the unprotected network side of the microchip, thereby not restricting network operations conducted by the microchip with said network, which network operations are conducted in said unprotected network side using said at least one network side general purpose microprocessor of the microchip when the computer is connected to said network; and
said computer is surrounded by a first Faraday Cage.
